51. Cell Stem Cell. 2018 Mar 1;22(3):290-291. doi: 10.1016/j.stem.2018.02.010.Organoid Models of Cancer Explode with Possibilities.Muthuswamy SK(1).Author information: (1)Cancer Center, Departments of Medicine and Pathology, Beth Israel DeaconessMedical Center, Harvard Medical School, Boston, MA, USA. Electronic address:smuthusw@bidmc.harvard.edu.Organoids have tremendous promise for modeling human cancers and revealing newbiological insights. Sachs et al. (2018), Seino et al. (2018) (in this issue ofCell Stem Cell), and Broutier et al. (2017) derive cancer organoids from breast, pancreas, and liver, respectively, not only reporting new methodologies but also showing their utility for translational and clinical cancer research.Copyright © 2018 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.DOI: 10.1016/j.stem.2018.02.010 PMID: 29499146 